author: dblevins
msg: ngs back to the way they were.

objectOutput.writeObject( externalizable )  -- Involves lots of reflection, cache checks, and extra data written to the stream.  After all that, the writeExternal method is called via reflection where and actual data is written.
externalizable.writeExternal(objectOutput) -- Faster, no reflection, uses less bandwidth, just writes data.
